parser.xmlParsing

Class ElementList

  • java.lang.Object
    • parser.xmlParsing.ElementList

  • public class ElementList
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is designed to hold an Element representing the head of a tree and extracts the data relevant for the database from its children

    • Method Detail

      • updateSpeaker

        private java.lang.String updateSpeaker(org.jdom2.Element currentElement)
        After going to the next line, the speaker has to be updated if possible (not for stage-directions etc.)
        Will set currentSpeaker to null if no speaker can be found.
        Parameters:
        currentElement - The element from which the speaker will be read if possible
        Returns:
        The speaker of the currentElement or empty String, if no speaker

      • addTweet

        line - What was said. If "", no tweet will be added

        Recursively goes through the XML and creates Tweets when necessary
        Parameters:
